    'topic' => 'What will the first adventures be?',
    'body' => 'Greetings All:

Not to take away the fun of the Starship Design Debate, but anybody had any
wishes of what the first adventures to be published will be like?

Personally, I\'d like to see a few "mysteries of the deep" adventures like
Twilight\'s Peak and Secre of the Ancients (Classic Traveller). Not
necessarily involving the Ancients, but sector-spanning adventures that take
you to several locales, while searching for clues to a greater mystery (since
we are coming out of the Long Night, maybe locating old technology, mapping
old colonies/bases, etc. could be the "push" here). Plenty of room for lots
of red herrings here!

Love them red herrings!

Another adventure I\'d like to see would be of a more limited scope. A
commercial-oriented adventure, where Traders are involved in setting up a
merchant company. This adventure would be (I think) suited for solitaire as
well as group play. Give lots of details on finance, stock markets and the
like--how the arrival of a rival ahead of you ruins the worth of your cargo.
It\'s a bare bones idea right now, but there might be something here (or I\'ve
been working in the finance industry--yech--too long!).

Finally, I\'d like to see Trillion Credit Squadron. Well, since it\'s an
earlier time, maybe we can call it Billion Credit Squadron. TCS accomplished
a lot of stuff that Battle Rider and others did--but with a lot less chrome.
I still have fond memories of designing ships with HG, outfitting a fleet,
and battling it out by plotting on graph paper with pencils and **big**
erasers! The campaign outlined in TCS would work, with some alterations. Just
have the lost colony get moved closer to where the Imperium is emerging from
the Long Night, change some tech levels, and there you go!

Thanks for listening.

Fred Kiesche
(FKiesche3@aol.com)

