    'index' => 'ad750',
    'topic' => 'Advanced Char Generation',
    'body' => 'One of the eternal problems with RPG Char Generation is this.  If I want to
generate an Advanced Character that is a Computer Programmer, like Myself,
then that is not really a problem.  However, much of the knowledge I have is
very specialized, and in most games rolled up into 1-3 skills, Computer, or
Computer Operations, Computer Programming, and Computer Build/Repair.

Now in a basic system, I could generate a basic character with a Computer 6
that would kick butt.  he could hack, repair, write, program, etc.  In an
advanced system, this same character might have 2-3 times as many skills.
Most of them would be, however, duplicates of the basic Computer Skill.  So
now I purchase a Programming Languages skill (to let me know if I can
decipher the code written by another programmer in a Language I don\'t know),
A Computer Operations skill (to simulate using software written by others),
a Computer Ettiqutte skill, a Networkig skill, a Communications skill, etc
ad nauseum.

In military terms the same things apply.  If I create a Merc charcater, just
how useful is his Heavy Weapons 4 skill when he is tailing someone?  Every
skill in traveller could be subskilled out to a great degree.  I mean think
of what you could use Streetwise for.  

I would love to see advanced char gen for other occupations.  I once
generated a rather detailed Fighter Pilot generation system for CT/MT.  It
was very Book 5 like with special assignments, etc.  It was chock full of
useful skills (for a fighter pilot) Heavy Figter Pilot, Medium Fighter
Pilot, Small Fighter Pilot, Fighter Tactics, Squadron Communiations,
Carousing, etc.  It was also quite leathal as I remember.  Survival rolls
were often above 7.  I test generated about 50 characters both enlisted and
officer and generated about 12 new types of fighters and fighter weapons. (A
ECM fighter for jamming, a Torpedo bomber complete with 5 ton missle,
atmospheric fighters, etc.)  It added a lot to our play, even though almost
every character generated with it didn\'t get a chance to fly a fighter in a
space battle.  

Were these characters BETTER then the others.  No, they were more detailed
about one aspect of their natures, but they were weak in other areas.  The
Fighter pilot just wasn\'t very good at finding cargo, or making deals with
Vargr, etc.  The saem could be said for Scientists, is it better to have
Science 5 , or Aquatic Biology 2, Volcanic Geology 1, etc.

DCB
