    'body' => 'On  5 Jun 96 at 18:26, CardSharks@aol.com spewed:

> Draft List (Subject to Revision).
> This list provides the basic character types and the range of skills which
> will be available in the character generation process in T4.

My Cr 0.02 on your efforts

> 
> Character types supported include:
> 
> Army, Navy, Marine, Scout, Merchant,
> Noble, Performer, Scholar, Agent, Rogue.

I hope there are plans at some point in the future to create other 
character classes as a supplement, in JTAS, or something...  I kind 
of miss the Pirate & Belter classes.  I suppose Scholar could replace 
Scientist (another of my faves).

> 
> Consolidated Skill List (* indicates Default Skills [see below])
> Archeology (one of many "Majors" for the Scholar character type).

I like the inclusion of more scientific disciplines.

> Archery*
> Armorer

Not sure I like giving characters the ability to build their own 
armor...sounds like a heap o\' trouble to me.  I\'ve run many an 
adventure where Merc type characters have been looking for a source 
to buy battle dress.  Now all they need to do is find the materials...

> Fast Talk*

What the heck is Fast Talk?  Is this the ability to be an auctioneer. 
 Or the ability to talk somebody into (or out of) something they 
really wouldn\'t do under most circumstances?

> First Aid* (very high levels become EMT)

Overall, I gotta agree with other peoples assessment on this 1.  I don\'t see a 
need for this, when most of the skills are duplicated by Medic-1 & 2. 

I suppose you could give this instead of Medic for military careers.  
A lot of folks would be taught First Aid in the army, not as many 
would actually go through Medical school.

> Performance (Art)
> Performance (Dance)
> Performance (Drama)
> Performance (Music)
> Performance (Writing)

Obvious choices for the Performer character.  I think the Performer 
type is tough to justify as a basic character class though.  I can\'t 
see too many people in Traveller playing this as a PC.  Hard to get 
excited about having rolled up a character with Performance (Dance)-4 
skill, when your neighbor is a Battle Dress-3, or Broker-2.  Would be a 
good type for a \'Citizens\' supplement though, and I can see some great 
ideas for NPC\'s & patrons.

> Psionicology (an academic endeavor)

Great idea in a pre-Psionic Suppressions Imperium

> *Default Skill (A character can always try a task at using one of these
> default skills at level 0). This is not an especially lucrative endeavor, but
> it does have some chance of success.
> 

I like the inclusion of a larger number of Default skills.

Very nice ideas, Marc.  Thanks for posting them.

