    'file' => 'XBOAT96A/XBT96063.TXT',
    'id' => undef,
    'body' => 'What an excellent idea!  Don\'t forget that we\'re talking about 1100 years of
the Imperium, too, and language can change dramatically in that time, so our
definitions and etymologies should perhaps also indicate the time when the
word was introduced into the language.

My girlfriend Carol Rhodes invented this word in about 1983:

cerastic (ser a\' stik) noun (from Terran English ca. -2400, ceramic +
plastic): Any fired synthetic material, typically used in furniture,
consoles, and dining ware aboard starships.  Cerastic is usually strong,
easy to clean and sterilize, and resistant to heat.  adjective:  being made
by cerastic process or of cerastic.


