    'year' => 1996,
    'index' => 'ad773',
    'topic' => ' Draft skills list',
    'body' => 'At 12:52 PM 6/6/96 -0400, you wrote:
>Archery		not default.
   Maybe not a default skill, but many people may have an Archery-0, not 
   bad enough to kill themselves, but not good enough to claim an archery
   skill.  Example, spent a week at Camp Scout-o-rama as a 12 year old. 
   Learned the basics, but not much more.

>Athletics	C	(Choose running, swimming, climbing, or a sport)
   I think this should be Performer (Sport -- Choose)

>Blade Weapons	DC	(Choose short blade, long blade, short club, long club)
        Clubs are not blade weapons and fit with Brawling (Armed)
>Brawling 	D       (Armed, Unarmed)
>Camouflage	D
    This should not be a default skill.  Two years of ROTC in college and
    I couldn\'t camouflage myself.  

>Disguise	D
    Not sure this should be defaulted either.  Do it poorly, and you stand out
    even more.

>Equestrian	not default.  
>[perhaps this should simply be placed under vehicle as one of the options.]

Not a default, except on Low tech worlds.

>First Aid	D? (very high levels become EMT)
Unsure about the Default level or not.  Most people know how to put a bandaid
on and clean simple wounds.  Does this warrent a Medic-0 or First Aid-0.  If this is not combined with Medic, then Medic-1 has to equal First Aid-4 or 
something like that.  A doctor is trained at those things at a higher level
than EMTs.  They should be combined because its a logical progression.
     Medic-0  First Aid
     Medic-1  EMT/Nurse
     Medic-2  Paramedic/Registered Nurse
     Medic-3  Doctor
     Medic-4  Specialist etc.

>GEOLOGY has been added, and there should be a note that players/GMs may 
>make up new majors

Good!.

>Grav Craft	D
   Only at TL-x and above....

>Leadership	D?
If you are defaulting things like investigation, interrogation, and such,
this one fits those kinds of skills.  Default it.

>Pilot
I wonder if we really need this.  Most of space travel is either
ships boat (in system), or astrogation (jump).  Pilot seems to have
less and less importance.  You have vehicle-ground, vehicle-sea, vehicle-air,
vehicle-grav, why not vehicle-space.  The only reason to keep it with Astrogation around is for compatiblity.

>Recon		D
Not sure about this one being default.

>Ships Boat 
(see comments about pilot)
>Trader		D
>Vacc Suit	D
Only at TL-x and above.

>Watercraft	D 
Having just gotten a boat, You need training and practice.  Not everyone is going to know how to operate a boat, where most adults know how to operate a car.  Probably should not default this, unless Hydro>=9.

Rob


- --
Rob Miracle
TanSoft.com
