..and now back to the subject of WHY ARE COMPUTERS SO BIG?

>Reason One for difference: Traveller was written in the mid-1970s.
>We werent wired then they way we are now and nobody really thought
>wed advance as quickly. 

True! <G> 

>Reason Two for difference: Most of the ships in the Traveller
>universe are built for rough travel.  The computers are built
>military style--ultra-rough and tough to take a lot of
>punishment.

Also probably true!

>Reason Three for difference: (Long ago), humaniti had much better
