shots in the advertisements and trailers contained only the best, most
interesting scenes in the entire movie?  After watching an episode of S:AAB I
noticed that they like to give you little glimpses into what is going to happen
in the rest of the show before going to a commercial break (gee, thanks).
Sentinel, on the other hand, likes to show you what happened *earlier* in the
episode before going to a commercial break (hey, the show\'s filmed here in
Vancouver, I\'ve got to at least give it a chance  8-)

=> Good news is that with the Mililieu system that IG is proposing, the 
=> basic rules are going to be just that (basic rules).  The background 
=> material for the particular era will be in a seperate supplement.  
