    'index' => 'ad886',
    'body' => 'After reading all the posts on Religious Scholars I thought I would try my
hand at creating a class
for such a character.  Here it is with a example of how it can be used.  

- -Daniel

****************************
Religious Scholar


Re-enlistment:  If the character has Admin skill they may use it as a
positive DM when attempting
to re-enlist.  A roll of 2 always means force retirement.  There is no
mandatory re-enlistment on a
roll of 12.

Skill eligibility:  During the first term of service the character is
eligible for two skills.  Each term
after that they are eligible for only one skill.  The character is also
eligible for one skill with each
distinction earned.

* Language Skill:  While not official canon it has been used in some of the
Alien modules.  The  *
religious Scholar would no doubt learn to read some long dead language to
help further their 
* studies.

Distinctions:  A character is eligible for only one distinction per term of
service.

Automatic skills:   Upon enlistment Language - 1.  Upon receiving first
distinction Admin - 1.

Mustering Out:  One benefit roll is allowed per term of service.  characters
who have received one
distinction are allowed one additional roll.  Characters who have received
two distinctions are
allowed two additional rolls.  Characters who have received three or more
distinctions are
allowed three additional rolls.  A maximum of three rolls are allowed on the
cash benefits table; all
additional rolls must be taken on the material benefits table.  Characters
who have served five or
more terms may add 1 to their rolls on the cash benefits table.  Characters
who have received two
or more distinctions may add 1 to their rolls on the material benefits table.

Enlistment     8+
     dm   +1 if Intelligence 8+
     dm   +2 if Education A+

Survival  5+
     dm   +2 if Social Standing 8+

Distinction    11+
     dm   +1 for each previous term of service

Re-enlistment  5+
     dm   + Admin skill level

Skills:
Personal                  	Education
1.   -1 Strength		Computer
2.   +1 Endurance		Language
3.   +1 Intelligence		Vehicle
4.   +1 Education		Admin
5.   Carousing		Brawling
6.   Bribery		Gun Cmbt

Advanced Education      	 Advanced Education (Education 8+)
1.   Computer       		Medical
2.   Language       		Language
3.   Vehicle        		Instruction
4.   Vacc Suit      		Admin
5.   +1 Education        	Jack o/a Trades
6.   Survival       		+1 Social Standing

Mustering Out:
Cash Benefits       	Material Benefits
1.   1000     	 -
2.   1000      	Low Passage
3.   2000      	Hand Computer
4.   5000      	Mid Passage
5.   10000         	 Weapon
6.   20000          	+1 Education
7.   40000          	+1 Social Standing

****************************

Religious Scholar Example:

**Hodgie, having finished school, decides that studying the long dead
Thistian religion would be
a grand way to spend his life.  Taking stock of himself [ player rolls 7, C,
7, 3, A, 9 ] he finds his
UPS is 7C73A9.  Not to bad.  He visits his home planets university and
attempts to gain
admission to the school of theology.  [ Player rolls a 6 (dm +2 for Educ +8)
giving an 8 ]  Hodgie
manages to pass the schools entrance exam.

**First Term:  His first term of service is rather uneventful.  [ For
survival player rolls a 9 (dm + 2
for Social Standing 8+) giving an 11]  But Hodgie has not yet distinguished
himself in his
published findings.  [ For distinction player rolls a 4 ]  The good news is
that Hodgie is able to
continue his studies for another year.  [ For re-enlistment player rolls a 7
].  Hodgie is eligible for
two skills this term plus automatically receives one level of Language
skill.  [ The GM tells the
player that the Language-1 skill is in Lagian, the Thistians long dead
language]  Working as a
scholar provides few physical challenges so to keep fit Hodgie takes up
martial arts as a hobby.  
[ Player rolls a 5 on skill table 2 \'Brawling\' (The GM takes note of this
and later creates an NPC
for Hodgies marital arts instructor!) ]  

Hodgies work also requires long sessions on the computer analyzing cryptic
ancient writings.  
[ Player rolls a 1 on table 3 \'Computer\' (GM takes note of this and later
details where these
ancient writings came from and how the university got a hold of them!) ]

** Second Term:  During his second four years of study, while in the field
looking for more of
those ancient writings, Hodgie has a very close call.  [ For survival player
rolls a 3 (dm +2 for
Social Standing 8+) giving a 5 (GM takes note of this and determines which
planet Hodgie was
on! ) ] 

Obviously the close call was worth it because Hodgie earned the distinction
of his peers!  
[ For distinction player rolls a 10 (dm +1 for one previous term) giving an
11 (GM takes note of
this and later determines that Hodgie uncovered the fabled long lost Spear
of the first Thistain
Saint!) ].     

Hodgie is eligible for two skills this term plus receives an automatic skill
level in Admin.  

His discovery of the long lost Thistian Spear has attracted the attention of
a powerful Noble, who
sponsors Hodgie for an increase in Social Standing.  [ Player rolls a 6 on
table 4 \'+1 Social
Standing\'  (GM selects or creates the Noble and develops suitable
background.  Hodgie now has
at lest one powerful friend!) ]

Now that Hodgie has been with the school of theology for several years he
has been asked to take
on a student and teach her the ropes.  [ Player rolls a 2 on table 4
\'Instruction\'  (GM creates an
NPC student for Hodgie and save her for later use!) ]  

Also because of his distinction Hodgie now finds it easier to get grant
money for further studies,
but learning to deal with the applications is a pain!  [ Automatic skill
level in \'Admin\' (GM creates
several companies and governments willing to fund studies into the Thistian
religion!) ]

With everything looking up for Hodgie bad news is hard to take!  [ For
re-enlistment player rolls a
2 \'Forced retirement!\' (GM takes note of this and secretly determines that a
mysterious rival had
gotten Hodgie kicked out by blackmailing the head of the theology school! ) ]

**Mustering out:  Hodgie is eligible for 3 mustering out benefits.  [
Players makes all three on the
Material Benefits table.  The three rolls are 4, 5 and 5 \'Mid passage\' and
\'Weapon\' twice.  Player
selects a revolver and then takes a skill in revolver ]

**Recap:  Hodgie is now 26 years old.  His UPS is 7C73AA and he  has the
following skills:  
Language - 1 (In Lagian), Instruction - 1, Admin -1, Brawling -1, Computer
- -1 and Revolver -1.
His only possessions are a revolver and a middle passage.  He spent eight
years studying the
ancient Thistain religion and recently made an import discovery in his
field.  For which he was
rewarded with social advancement.

He has three NPC contacts, his martial arts instructor, a powerful noble and
his former student. 
But he also has a rival who is black mailing the head of his former theology
school.  

Also, Hodgie knows of several companies that might be willing to provide
private funding for
more research, if he can make his case to them.

****************

IMO details and background are what make for an interesting charator, not
pages of little used (or
understood) skills!  

Comments welcome

- -Daniel


