database tuning.  Know a few other bits and pieces about this and that.  In
the office we also have some folks who are computer-4 but their
specialization is GIS systems.  What can we discuss?  The weather.  If I
tried to do their work, I would be about a computer-0.

Creep seems to happen most often in military skills probably because (1) a
lot of gamers are military buffs, or have picked up a fair amount of
military knowledge from gaming and (2) things which can leave my character
dead are VERY interesting.

The result? It seems resonable to have a skill cascade Foward
Observer(Ortillery) but only one History skill as if a professor of
Victorian Social Anthropology could make a meaning statement of New Kingdom
Physical Culture.

What soultion would I propose?  Drag it back -- simplify.  Assume NPC
specialists are specialists (a few side skills for depth, but the lad with
the radio and the laser designator is the FO and that\'s it).  Let players be
generalists.  I would sooner have a player with skill Grunt-5 who can be a
one man army then to have to deal with all gory details (yes, you have
Combat Rifle-17, but that\'s a smoothbore, it doesn\'t count?)

