The ostensible reason for the IN placing an interdiction on Shionthy
was that the concentration of contra-terrene matter was a significant
hazard to space travel. A single fleck of antimatter could severely damage a
ship, and probably the crew as well due to the radiation produced in
the annihilation. Adventure 1: The Kinunir gives some rules for
encountering antimatter, so I think that this could be taken as
official canon.

Of course, since the Shionthy belt is presumed to have been caused by
a Ancient planet-buster weapon, the Imperial Navy have probably
interdicted the system so that they can sift the area for scraps of
Ancient technology without treasure hunters making off with valuable
(and possibly powerful) items.

If I remember rightly, the Travellers Digest published an adventure
(part of the grand tour) which took place on an interdicted Ancient
site in the Marches, but I can\'t remember which system it was on
(Pixie springs to mind, though).

