    'year' => 1996,
    'index' => 'ae094',
    'body' => 'Has anybody designed asteroid-based SDBs or stationary \'rock fortress\' in
their time? I have an old design (using HG, Book 5) but it\'s jump capable - I\'d 
like to see how other people optimise them for SDB deployment.

Also I\'d like to see some new ideas on disguise for this sort of ship; eg in
my ship, I have installed thrusters with extensive battery banks so it can
operate with its fusion plant shut down, the asteroid is nickel-iron with 
carbonaceous coating to absorb light, and the thruster radiator fins are 
recessed into a crater at the back of the asteroid so its EM signature is 
reduced. Other features (EM arrays, weapon bays, airlocks, fighter/small craft 
