I have Glimmerdrift & Ley as well.  I\'ve used them several times for 
campaigns in the past.  I was never sure why GDW declared them 
heretical, er, non "canon"  I also had Maranantha-Alkahest & Gateway. 
The nice thing about them was that they all linked together when at the time 
the only other published sectors out there were Spinward Marches 
(which GDW beat like a dead horse in the CT era), and Solomani Rim 
(which during the pre-Rebellion era was frankly a pretty boring place 
to adventure for the most part).  Having 4 cohesive sectors, most of 
which the Imperium had little or no control of, gave plenty of 
opportunities for far-flung campaigns...

> Trouble is, the very positions of the stars are different! We know *that* much
> from the Atlas of the Imperium, and a few other supplements that had star maps
> that more or less covered that area. <<

Frankly, Atlas of the Imperium wasn\'t all that great, and conflicted 
with other sources, including GDW\'s in some instances...

> I\'ve used Beyond and Vanguard Reaches for years; GDW declared rather pompously
> that they weren\'t "real" but then didn\'t deign to provide anything official to
> use instead, jut hints. Stuff it. In _my_ Known Space, the Beyond is still right
> there.

What the heck, its not like anybody designed some to replace them.  
You\'d STILL have to design 1 of your own if you decided to run your 
campaign there.  So why not use them if you got them.  

Stu 
