This needs to be very carefully done. If a new drive technology comes 
along which is (a) cheaper and (b) better -- more efficient, whatever 
- -- than the current drive, there are going to be *major* economic 
effects. That means economic dislocation, civil war, strife and many 
other things which are going to reduce the quality of life for 
players.

The whole question rests on economics. If your new FTL technology 
isn\'t better (cheaper to run/but or faster or whatever) nobody\'s 
going to use it. Look at how Wankel rotary engines failed to take off 
(it\'s arguable that these in fact were superior to standard internal 
combustion engines, but from what I can recall they suffered serious 
reliability problems). If it is better, everyone is going to use it 
and after a while the old technology falls out of use.

